      "source_region_type": "text_span",
      "source_locator_text": "Herein we report the formulation of GAR entrapped PLGA nanoparticles by nanoprecipitation method using vitamin E TPGS as an emulsifier.",
      "supporting_text": "Herein we report the formulation of GAR entrapped PLGA nanoparticles by nanoprecipitation method using vitamin E TPGS as an emulsifier."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "span_1",
      "source_region_type": "text_span",
      "source_locator_text": "Blank and GAR-loaded PLGA NPs were prepared through a nanoprecipitation technique using vitamin E TPGS as an emulsifier.",
      "supporting_text": "Blank and GAR-loaded PLGA NPs were prepared through a nanoprecipitation technique using vitamin E TPGS as an emulsifier."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "span_2",
      "source_region_type": "text_span",
      "source_locator_text": "Table 1 summarizes average size (Fig. 1a), zeta potential (Fig. 1b), drug loading, and encapsulation efficiency of blank and GAR-NPs.",
      "supporting_text": "Table 1 summarizes average size (Fig. 1a), zeta potential (Fig. 1b), drug loading, and encapsulation efficiency of blank and GAR-NPs."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "span_3",
      "source_region_type": "text_span",
      "source_locator_text": "Nanoprecipitation technique yielded GAR-NPs with most narrow size distribution (average diameter 88.05 ± 2.7 nm) as determined by dynamic light scattering (DLS) with a PDI value of 0.170 ± 0.05 and satisfactory zeta potential (−28.10 ± 2.1).",
      "supporting_text": "Nanoprecipitation technique yielded GAR-NPs with most narrow size distribution (average diameter 88.05 ± 2.7 nm) as determined by dynamic light scattering (DLS) with a PDI value of 0.170 ± 0.05 and satisfactory zeta potential (−28.10 ± 2.1)."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "span_4",
      "source_region_type": "text_span",
      "source_locator_text": "The particle size was slightly increased (Table 1 around 100 nm) with a moderate change in PDI value, whereas zeta potential showed the least variation; this suggested the satisfactory stability of GAR-NPs during storage.",
      "supporting_text": "The particle size was slightly increased (Table 1 around 100 nm) with a moderate change in PDI value, whereas zeta potential showed the least variation; this suggested the satisfactory stability of GAR-NPs during storage."
    },
    {
      "span_id": "span_5",
      "source_region_type": "text_span",
      "source_locator_text": "Drug loading amounts and encapsulation efficiencies of various GAR loaded nanoparticle formulations prepared by varying the amount of GAR and PLGA were measured.",
      "supporting_text": "Drug loading amounts and encapsulation efficiencies of various GAR loaded nanoparticle formulations prepared by varying the amount of GAR and PLGA were measured."
    },
    {
